197238.name: Indicator:Out-of-pocket expenditure (OOP) per capita in PPP int$
197238.description:
Rationale: This indicator estimates the average health expenditure through out-of-pocket payments per capita in comparable currency including the purchasing power of national currencies against USD. It indicates how much every person payts out of pocket on average in USD PPP at the point of use. High out of pocket payment are associated with catastrophic and impoverishing household spending. Out of pocket payment are not pooled and there is no sharing of risk among wider group of people other then the household. This indicator describes the OOP expenditure in relation to the population size and the purchasing power of the local currency facilitating international comparison.

Definition: Out-of-Pocket expenditure (OOP) per capita in Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) int$

Method of measurement: (HF.3)/population

Method of estimation: -
